## Remarks  
 You can specify the shape of the tip that is used to draw <xref:System.Windows.Ink.Stroke> objects by setting the <xref:System.Windows.Ink.DrawingAttributes.StylusTip%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property.  
  
<a name="xamlTextUsage_StylusTip"></a>   
## XAML Text Usage  
 This class is not typically used in XAML.  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 The following example demonstrates how to use two <xref:System.Windows.Ink.DrawingAttributes> objects to simulate using a pen and a highlighter on the same <xref:System.Windows.Controls.InkCanvas>. The highlighter's <xref:System.Windows.Ink.DrawingAttributes.StylusTip%2A> property is set to Rectangle.  
  
 The example assumes the root element in the "XAML" file is a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.DockPanel> called `root`. It also assumes that there is a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Button> called `btnToggleHighlighter` and that the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.ButtonBase.Click> event has been connected to the event handler.  
  
